00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:45.000
make 2-min quick time videos which are summaries of their presentations as well

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:52.000
and you could see those at steveblank.com/slides but if you want to actively engage in the class,

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:58.000
your first real homework is download that Osterwalder canvas and using yellow stickies,

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:04.000
take a shot at actually filling out all your hypothesis on the business model canvass.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
It's okay if you're just guessing because the whole class is about

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:09.000
how do you turn those guesses into facts.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:16.000
So get ready, download the canvas, put on those yellow stickies, and then looking at those boxes,

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:24.000
start figuring out who would you call on and who would you contact to start testing those hypothesis

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:30.000
and take a look for the first week at your value proposition and customer segment box.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:35.000
Who would you want to talk to, to validate whether your idea about what features are important

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:39.000
and who would you talk to, to validate that these are customers you want to go after

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:43.000
and we're just getting you ready for the work you're going to do after the next lecture.

00:01:43.000 --> 99:59:59.000
